text: José Castro (1808–1860) was a native governor of Alta California. José Castro may also refer to: *José Ribeiro e Castro (born 1957), Portuguese politician *José Castro (baseball) (born 1958), professional baseball coach *José Castro (fencer) (born 1928), Portuguese Olympic fencer *José Castro (sport shooter) (born 1907), Brazilian Olympic shooter *José Castro (water polo) (born 1915), Uruguayan Olympic water polo player *José Antonio Castro (born 1980), Mexican football player *José Bañales Castro (born 1960), Mexican politician *José Alberto Castro (born 1963), Mexican producer and director *José de Castro (1868–1929), Portuguese lawyer, journalist and politician *José María Castro Madriz, Costa Rican lawyer, academic, diplomat, and politician
title: José Castro (disambiguation)
